    <section>
        <h2>Question 1: What is microbiology?</h2>
        <p>Microbiology is the study of microorganisms, including bacteria, viruses, fungi, and protozoa.</p>

        <h2>Question 2: What are the main types of microorganisms?</h2>
        <p>The main types of microorganisms include bacteria, viruses, fungi, and algae.</p>

        <h2>Question 3: What is the role of bacteria in the ecosystem?</h2>
        <p>Bacteria play crucial roles in nutrient cycling, such as decomposing organic matter and fixing nitrogen.</p>

        <h2>Question 4: What is a pathogen?</h2>
        <p>A pathogen is any microorganism that causes disease in a host organism.</p>

